erryronald.com TerryRonald.com]\n}}\n'''Terry Maxwell Ronald''' is an [[English people|English]] author, singer, songwriter, and music producer.\n\n==Biography==\nBorn in South London, Ronald was a founder member and lead singer with the pop band ''[[Gun Shy (band)|Gun Shy]]'',<ref name=SSG/> who released one single \"Just To Be Your Secret\",<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.discogs.com/Gun-Shy-Just-To-Be-Your-Secret/release/1757743 |title=Gun Shy - Just To Be Your Secret (Vinyl) at Discogs |publisher=Discogs.com |date= |accessdate=2014-06-06}}</ref> which was [[Peter Powell (disc jockey)|Peter Powell]]'s record of the week on [[BBC Radio 1|Radio One]]. In the early 1990s, Ronald released solo album \"Roma\" on [[MCA Records]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.discogs.com/Terry-Ronald-Chains-Of-Love/release/2095464 |title=Terry Ronald - Roma (CD, Album) at Discogs |publisher=Discogs.com |date= |accessdate=2014-06-06}}</ref><ref name=RHBio/> from which four singles were released.\n\nRonald developed his career as a melody writer and lyricist, usually working with another writer. His musical work includes songwriting, production and vocal arranging for [[Kylie Minogue]], [[Girls Aloud]], [[Dannii Minogue]], [[Sophie Ellis-Bextor]], [[The Wanted]], [[Westlife]], [[The Saturdays]],  [[Lulu (singer)|Lulu]], [[Sheena Easton]], [[Kim Wilde]], [[Atomic Kitten]], [[Geri Halliwell]], [[Elouise]] and French pop starlet [[Lorie (singer)|Lorie]].<ref name=SSG/><ref name=RHBio/> In 2007, he appeared as a guest judge on the Judges' Homes section of The X Factor, alongside Dannii Minogue.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.terryronald.com/biography/ |title=\u00bb Biography Terry Ronald |publisher=Terryronald.com |date= |accessdate=2014-06-06}}</ref> He has  worked as a vocal coach on music TV shows including ''The Voice'', ''The Voice Kids'', ''All Together Now'' and ''Let's Sing & Dance For Comic Relief''.\n\nRonald has worked on the creative team of several West End theatre productions, including Rent Remixed, which starred [[Denise Van Outen]], Siobhan Donaghy and Luke Evans,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.classicalsource.com/db_control/db_concert_review.php?id=5034 |title=Rent Remixed - from www.classicalsource.com |publisher=Classicalsource.com |date=2007-10-16 |accessdate=2014-06-06}}</ref> and The Hurly Burly Show.<ref name=SSG>{{cite web|url=http://sosogay.co.uk/2011/interview-terry-ronald/|title=Interview: Terry Ronald|author=Alasdair Spiv|publisher=So So Gay|date=16 March 2011|accessdate=25 January 2014}}</ref> In 2013 Ronald co-wrote the musical one-woman play ''[[Some Girl I Used To Know]]'' with Denise Van Outen.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.whatsonstage.com/birmingham-theatre/news/10-2013/denise-van-outen-tours-one-woman-show-next-year_32317.html |title=Denise Van Outen tours one-woman show next year - Theatre News - 16 Oct 2013 |publisher=Whatsonstage.com |date= |accessdate=2014-06-06}}</ref>\n\nIn 2010, he wrote his first novel ''[[Becoming Nancy]]'',<ref name=RHBio>{{cite web|url=http://www.randomhouse.co.uk/authors/terry-ronald|title=Author: Terry Ronald|publisher=[[Random House]]|accessdate=25 January 2014}}</ref> published in April 2011 by Transworld and described by Suzy Feay in [[The Independent]] as \"a deliciously camp rites of passage novel\".<ref>{{cite web|author=Suzi Feay |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/books/features/max-wallis-and-the-award-for-savage-wit-goes-to-8348229.html |title=Max Wallis: 'And the award for savage wit goes to ...' - Features - Books |publisher=The Independent |date=2012-11-25 |accessdate=2014-06-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.between-the-lines.co.uk/?p=1284 |title=What Shall I Read? \u00bb Dannii dazzles at best friend Terry Ronald\u2019s launch party |publisher=Between-the-lines.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2014-06-06}}</ref> The book was shortlisted for the 2012 Polari First Book Prize, and in January 2014 it was announced that [[Tony Award]]-winning director and choreographer [[Jerry Mitchell]] had bought the rights to the musical stage version of the book, which is set to open in the U.S in 2019 at the [[Alliance Theatre]] in Atlanta. <ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.broadwayworld.com/article/Jerry-Mitchell-to-Adapt-Terry-Ronalds-BECOMING-NANCY-to-Stage-Musical-20140124 |title=Jerry Mitchell to Adapt Terry Ronald's BECOMING NANCY to Stage Musical |publisher=Broadwayworld.com |date= |accessdate=2014-06-06}}</ref>\n\n<br />\n\n==Personal life==\nRonald lives in East Dulwich, South London with his [[civil partner]], Mark.<ref name=RHBio/>\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Solo albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#ebf5ff;\"\n! Year !! Album / Year of release !! Singles\n|-\n|1990\n|\n*''[[Studio Sessions (Terry Ronald album)|Studio Sessions]]''\n|\n*\n*Contains live studio recordings from ''Roma'' and two cover songs\n|-\n|1991\n|Roma\n|\n*Calm the Rage\"\n*\"[[Chains of Love (Terry Ronald song)|Chains of Love]]\"\n*\"[[One More Dollar]]\"\n*\"[[What the Child Needs]]\"\n*Sweet Sound Of Love\n*Save Me From Myself\n*Live Forever\n*Red\n*All I Wanted was To Love You\n*Hearts & Flowers\n*Cold Heart\n*48 Hours\n|-\n|2019\n|Underworld Gospel EP\n|My Underworld\nWhat The Child Needs\n\nChild Theme\n\nUnderworld Gospel\n\nGospel Reprise\n|}\n\n===Solo singles===\n{| class=\"sortable\"\n|- style=\"background:#ebf5ff;\"\n! Year !! Single / Release date / Label !! Tracks\n|-\n|1990\n|\n*\"Calm the Rage\"\n*Released: June 1990\n*Label: [[Music Corporation of America|MCA]]\n|\n*\"Calm the Rage\" (Ronald/Lowis)\n*\"The Longest Time (Live)\" (Ronald/Hallawell)\n|-\n|1991\n|\n*\"[[Chains of Love (Terry Ronald song)|Chains of Love]]\"\n*Released: February 1991\n*Label: [[Music Corporation of America|MCA]]\n|\n*\"Chains of Love\" (Ronald/Lowis)\n*\"Slaves\" (Ronald/Connelly)\n*\"For What It's Worth\" (featuring [[Linda Lewis]]) (S Stills)\n|-\n|1991\n|\n*\"[[One More Dollar]]\"\n*Released: May 1991\n*Label: [[Music Corporation of A